The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Sri Lanka hire Sandy Gordon

Colombo: Sri Lanka have hired leading sports psychologist Sandy Gordon to try and arrest the teams plummeting confidence ahead of a difficult triangular series against Australia and South Africa. 

Sri Lanka have lost eight out of their last nine one-day Internationals and suffered series defeats to India and New Zealand in the process, causing the side to fall from second to sixth in the ICC ODI rankings. 

We are in serious trouble, Sri Lanka Crickets (SLC) chief executive Duleep Mendis said. (AGENCIES) 




